					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">1. Rising edge of A12.  The A13 line is not connected to the MMC3 anyway.
<br />
<br />2. The scanline before VBlank does not clock the MMC3.  The dummy scanline after VBlank does.  In short, the MMC3 will be clocked 241 times per scanline (assuming normal pattern table configurations).
<br />
<br />3. Yes.  Games using CHR-RAM have to write to $8000/1 at startup to ensure that the CHR-RAM is properly seen by the PPU.
<br />
<br />4. The horizontal scroll registers are reset to the latch at cycle 257 of each scanline.  The vertical registers are incremented at cycle 251 of each scanline.  During the pre-render scanline, all registers (horizontal and vertical) are reset at cycle 304.  (These timings assume cycles 0-255 corresponding to on-screen drawing and 256-340 corresponding to HBlank.)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

