						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">darklink wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">games with VRAM usually of 8K size, right ?</div>
<br />Only a few games have CHR RAM larger than 8 KiB. The only one I can think of is <em>Videomation</em>, on a CPROM board, which has 16 KiB.
<br />
<br />A few MMC3 games use mappers with both CHR RAM and CHR ROM. These include the Rare pinball sims that use the TQROM board (<em>Pinbot</em> and <em>High Speed</em>), which have an 8 KB CHR RAM bank in addition to CHR ROM, and a couple Chinese RPGs on a functionally similar board that copy Chinese character glyphs from PRG ROM to CHR RAM.</div>

